==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Massage
<hw>Mas"sage</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety> <def>A
rubbing or kneading of the body, especially when performed as a hygienic
or remedial measure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Massage</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Massage
<hw>Mas"sage</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>To treat by means of massage; to rub or knead; <as>as, to
<ex>massage</ex> a patient with ointment</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Massagist</ent>⟦br⟧
